Sharing a concrete script example that incorporates industry best practices can be a fantastic way to give students a head start on their learning journey. Here's a scenario and example script for an input form that participates in the full cycle from capturing the input to securely storing it:

**Scenario:**

Create a simple user registration form that captures the user's name, email, and password. The form should validate the input data, store it securely in a database, and provide a confirmation message to the user.

**Example Script:**

For this example, we'll use Node.js, Express.js, and MongoDB as the backend technology stack. We'll also use a library like bcrypt to securely hash and store the user's password.

**Frontend (HTML, CSS, JavaScript):**

```html
<!-- index.html -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>User Registration Form</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
  <h1>User Registration Form</h1>
  <form id="registration-form">
    <label for="name">Name:</label>
    <input type="text" id="name" name="name"><br><br>
    <label for="email">Email:</label>
    <input type="email" id="email" name="email"><br><br>
    <label for="password">Password:</label>
    <input type="password" id="password" name="password"><br><br>
    <button type="submit">Register</button>
  </form>
  <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

